1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Mojo-Mojo-Mojo-Spy

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Mojo-Mojo-Mojo-Spy

3
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:26,000
This world is full of colors bright

4
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
What truly tricks our eyes and sight

5
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Use your heart to see it clear

6
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,000
The truth is waiting, always near

7
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Hey you good or bad, truth or lies

8
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Can't escape the smoke that blinds

9
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Take your courage, stand up tall

10
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Maybe you can save it all

11
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Mojo Mojo Mojo Spy

12
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Mojo Mojo Mojo Spy

13
00:00:53,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Mojo Mojo Mojo Spy

14
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:47,500
Locky Qi gets dragged by Jingjing to see the gem Angel's Tears on display

15
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:58,500
But the gem is already gone without a trace

16
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:29,480
A hacker breaks into the museum's security system

17
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:29,480
And in the hall, a mysterious teen appears out of nowhere

18
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:29,500
Could it be him?

19
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:31,000
What do I do, what do I do? My uncle's not here yet

20
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,599
What do I do

21
00:01:33,599 --> 00:01:34,620
What do I do

22
00:01:34,620 --> 00:01:36,340
What do I do

23
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:36,780
What do I do

24
00:01:36,780 --> 00:01:38,040
What do I do

25
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:39,159
Screw it

26
00:01:39,159 --> 00:01:39,719
Stop right there.

27
00:01:39,719 --> 00:01:42,640
Who are you?

28
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:46,460
You sneaked into the vault like a crook,

29
00:01:46,460 --> 00:01:48,599
then rammed my ice cream with your car.

30
00:01:48,599 --> 00:01:49,780
What are you up to?

31
00:01:49,780 --> 00:01:52,799
Huh? What ice cream?

32
00:01:52,799 --> 00:01:55,719
Don't play dumb with me.

33
00:01:55,719 --> 00:01:58,340
You half-man, half-woman freak.

34
00:01:58,340 --> 00:02:02,340
You're dead meat!

35
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:16,340
Hmph, you're asking for it.

36
00:02:20,340 --> 00:02:21,340
Locky Qi.

37
00:02:22,340 --> 00:02:23,340
Locky Qi.

38
00:02:23,340 --> 00:02:28,340
Didn't expect a kid your age to be so ruthless.

39
00:02:28,340 --> 00:02:30,340
Criminal! Criminal!

40
00:02:30,340 --> 00:02:33,340
He must be the one who stole the gem.

41
00:02:35,340 --> 00:02:36,340
No.

42
00:02:36,340 --> 00:02:39,340
The culprit will always return to the crime scene.

43
00:02:39,340 --> 00:02:41,340
And you just entered the vault.

44
00:02:41,340 --> 00:02:43,340
So the criminal is you, you, you, you, you!

45
00:02:43,340 --> 00:02:44,340
I'm not.

46
00:02:44,340 --> 00:02:45,340
Say whatever you want.

47
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:47,340
Hand over the gem now!

48
00:02:47,340 --> 00:02:48,340
Rex.

49
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:50,340
Please calm down.

50
00:02:50,340 --> 00:02:51,340
Calm down.

51
00:02:51,340 --> 00:02:52,340
No matter what,

52
00:02:52,340 --> 00:02:54,340
you're now the prime suspect.

53
00:02:55,340 --> 00:02:57,340
Please come with us.

54
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:07,340
You were caught red-handed at the crime scene.

55
00:03:07,340 --> 00:03:08,340
Still trying to talk your way out?

56
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:16,340
I was conducting an investigation.

57
00:03:16,340 --> 00:03:17,340
Investigations are police business.

58
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:19,340
You're just a kid.

59
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:20,340
What are you butting in for?

60
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:22,840
Many cases are hard to solve on an organizational level.

61
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:25,120
So I have to step in as an individual.

62
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:29,460
Captain, I'm sure he's the culprit.

63
00:03:29,460 --> 00:03:32,939
I suggest you cooperate with us.

64
00:03:32,939 --> 00:03:35,099
After all, this isn't your home turf.

65
00:03:35,099 --> 00:03:37,759
Hawxing, little detective.

66
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:41,000
De... detective?

67
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:47,659
The famous young detective of Squid City.

68
00:03:47,659 --> 00:03:49,340
At such a young age,

69
00:03:49,340 --> 00:03:51,139
you possess outstanding detective reasoning talent.

70
00:03:51,139 --> 00:03:52,240
You travel far and wide,

71
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,419
helping police forces everywhere

72
00:03:53,419 --> 00:03:55,120
solve many tough cases.

73
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:57,120
Never thought I'd run into you here.

74
00:03:57,120 --> 00:04:00,139
So, little detective, after your personal investigation,

75
00:04:00,139 --> 00:04:02,359
what results have you got?

76
00:04:04,359 --> 00:04:06,400
I suspect it's the security guard, Ray.

77
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:09,519
Impressive, impressive.

78
00:04:09,519 --> 00:04:12,300
The genius detective truly lives up to the name.

79
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,879
Actually, Mr. K, who's managing this exhibition,

80
00:04:14,879 --> 00:04:16,220
also told me in private

81
00:04:16,220 --> 00:04:17,199
that he suspects Ray.

82
00:04:17,199 --> 00:04:19,319
But what evidence do you have

83
00:04:19,319 --> 00:04:21,459
to say he's the suspect?

84
00:04:21,459 --> 00:04:23,879
For now, my evidence isn't very solid.

85
00:04:23,879 --> 00:04:27,060
But my first instinct tells me

86
00:04:27,060 --> 00:04:29,420
Ray is very likely the culprit.

87
00:04:29,420 --> 00:04:33,000
I suppose the young detective knows

88
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,219
that to catch a suspect,

89
00:04:34,219 --> 00:04:36,120
you need solid evidence.

90
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:38,879
Just like how you sneaked into the vault

91
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:40,279
and got caught red-handed by us.

92
00:04:40,279 --> 00:04:41,819
We had plenty of evidence,

93
00:04:41,819 --> 00:04:44,560
and you became the prime suspect.

94
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:46,480
I was here to investigate.

95
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:48,200
If you give me enough time,

96
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:51,280
I'll find sufficient evidence to catch the culprit.

97
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:54,259
Fine. I trust your ability.

98
00:04:54,259 --> 00:04:56,340
I'll give you time to find the evidence.

99
00:04:56,340 --> 00:04:59,200
Another detective was supposed to assist you,

100
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,500
but he suddenly got another assignment.

101
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:05,200
So he asked his nephew Locky Qi to look for clues with you.

102
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:08,700
I don't need any help.

103
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:14,920
You're just letting him go like that?

104
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,780
My uncle is just lazy himself,

105
00:05:29,780 --> 00:05:30,680
but he insists on saying

106
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,660
he wants me to train my deduction skills.

107
00:05:32,660 --> 00:05:34,439
He told me to find the clues.

108
00:05:34,439 --> 00:05:35,939
Detective Locky Qi,

109
00:05:35,939 --> 00:05:37,460
buy Jingjing some juice.

110
00:05:37,460 --> 00:05:38,660
The meeting place with Mr. K

111
00:05:38,660 --> 00:05:39,580
should be right here.

112
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:44,300
My uncle's map is terrible.

113
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:46,300
Alright, let's go!

114
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:53,300
Ahhh, let me go, let me go!

115
00:05:54,300 --> 00:05:55,300
A kid your age coming to a bar?

116
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:56,300
Where are your parents?

117
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:58,300
I, the great detective, am here to solve a case, and you dare be rude?

118
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:02,300
My friend.

119
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:05,300
Hmph, so it's you, the suspect.

120
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:06,300
What are you doing here?

121
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:07,300
What are YOU doing here?

122
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:10,300
Hehe~ I'm handling a case.

123
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,300
I heard there's a detective fan

124
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:16,300
coming to assist me.

125
00:06:16,300 --> 00:06:18,300
That person is you, right?

126
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,300
Who? Who?

127
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,300
Who's the detective enthusiast?

128
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:23,300
I'll become a world-famous detective sooner or later.

129
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:26,300
Heh, look at you.

130
00:06:26,300 --> 00:06:28,300
A suspect caught red-handed.

131
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,300
And taken away by the cops.

132
00:06:29,300 --> 00:06:31,300
What's there to be cocky about?

133
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:33,300
Say that again.

134
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:34,300
Aha, a suspect.

135
00:06:34,300 --> 00:06:36,300
You wanna fight?

136
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:39,300
Oh ho ho~ I think everyone's thirsty.

137
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:42,300
Why don't we head to the restaurant across the street and chat over a drink?

138
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:48,759
Mr. K.

139
00:06:48,759 --> 00:06:52,180
I heard you're also suspicious of that guy, Reje.

140
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:54,180
Mm-hmm.

141
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:56,379
Ever since the gem went missing,

142
00:06:56,379 --> 00:06:58,879
I've noticed Reje acting really strange.

143
00:06:58,879 --> 00:07:01,840
Especially when the cops arrived at the scene,

144
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:03,780
he was unusually nervous.

145
00:07:03,780 --> 00:07:07,139
And when you were caught red-handed at the vault door,

146
00:07:07,139 --> 00:07:09,740
he jumped out especially excitedly to point fingers at you.

147
00:07:09,740 --> 00:07:12,280
Almost like he wanted to pin the crime on you.

148
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:14,200
My being caught—

149
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,080
no need to bring that up again.

150
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:18,400
But what I noticed at the time was...

151
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:20,540
Ray also wears one on his hand.

152
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:22,980
The same invisibility watch as mine.

153
00:07:25,980 --> 00:07:26,580
This invisibility watch

154
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:28,080
They were made by the military for secret agents.

155
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,100
Infiltrate the enemy's base.

156
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:30,840
The special tools they developed

157
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,760
The wearer can temporarily hide.

158
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:33,620
The electronic eye's surveillance footage.

159
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:34,940
Wear this watch

160
00:07:34,940 --> 00:07:36,220
Want to sneak into the museum?

161
00:07:36,220 --> 00:07:37,460
A piece of cake.

162
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:39,580
Just a broken watch.

163
00:07:39,580 --> 00:07:41,300
Does that prove he's guilty?

164
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:42,620
Mr. K

165
00:07:42,620 --> 00:07:45,040
You and Reggie both have keys to the vault.

166
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:47,800
You two are both suspects in the gem theft.

167
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:51,540
No no no no no

168
00:07:51,540 --> 00:07:54,360
This gem is a national treasure of our country.

169
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:57,300
The nation's treasures are basically my treasures.

170
00:07:57,300 --> 00:08:00,080
Why would I steal something that already belongs to me?

171
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:02,280
And if we don't get the gem back...

172
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:05,400
I... I can't go back like this.

173
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:10,340
On the night of the crime, what were you all doing?

174
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:13,420
That night

175
00:08:13,420 --> 00:08:16,040
We first met at that shop across the street.

176
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,900
A grown man drinking at a bar.

177
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:19,540
I can't hold my liquor well.

178
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:22,340
But Reijie kept pushing drinks on me.

179
00:08:22,340 --> 00:08:25,319
Then Reijie said I was too drunk.

180
00:08:25,319 --> 00:08:27,620
So he helped me to his apartment to rest.

181
00:08:27,620 --> 00:08:30,160
I remember as soon as we entered the building,

182
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,980
a doorman with a weird accent

183
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:32,879
cursed me out.

184
00:08:32,879 --> 00:08:35,019
I asked Reijie why we got yelled at.

185
00:08:35,019 --> 00:08:37,659
He said the apartment's curfew was 11 PM.

186
00:08:37,659 --> 00:08:39,680
We came back too late.

187
00:08:39,680 --> 00:08:41,039
The doorman was annoyed.

188
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:44,779
Then as soon as I got to his place, I couldn't stop throwing up.

189
00:08:44,779 --> 00:08:47,079
He said he'd find me a hangover cure.

190
00:08:47,079 --> 00:08:49,179
Told me to rest on the bed.

191
00:08:49,179 --> 00:08:52,779
I lay down and fell into a deep sleep.

192
00:08:52,779 --> 00:08:55,019
I don't know how long passed.

193
00:08:55,019 --> 00:08:56,559
Reijie woke me up.

194
00:08:56,559 --> 00:08:58,379
He found the hangover cure.

195
00:08:58,379 --> 00:09:00,679
I took it and felt super alert.

196
00:09:00,679 --> 00:09:03,259
Then we watched together

197
00:09:03,259 --> 00:09:06,079
the 11:30 PM live broadcast of

198
00:09:06,079 --> 00:09:08,039
the Smile Show.

199
00:09:08,039 --> 00:09:09,839
The show was fun.

200
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:12,000
After watching it,

201
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,940
We talked all the way till dawn.

202
00:09:14,940 --> 00:09:16,300
So that means

203
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:17,120
during the time of the crime,

204
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,000
he should have been with you

205
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,120
watching TV, right?

206
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:22,019
It's too early to jump to conclusions.

207
00:09:22,019 --> 00:09:24,139
Let's go check out Reggie's apartment together.

208
00:09:24,139 --> 00:09:30,840
I really don't want

209
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:35,040
to be alone and lonely.

210
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:38,460
Life can be

211
00:09:38,460 --> 00:09:42,960
a little unhappy sometimes.

212
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:46,080
Saying goodbye to today

213
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:50,480
always makes people feel lost.

214
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:53,940
Look at tomorrow

215
00:09:53,940 --> 00:09:58,220
waving to each other on the horizon.

216
00:09:58,220 --> 00:10:01,940
Every day goes by with sunrise and sunset,

217
00:10:01,940 --> 00:10:05,940
turning time into more fantasies.

218
00:10:05,940 --> 00:10:11,000
Looking forward to every second and every minute of life,

219
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:17,700
my bright eyes are sparkling.

220
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:21,080
A smile that greets the sunshine,

221
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:26,300
stepping through the screaming crossroads.

222
00:10:35,940 --> 00:10:37,940
I, Sima Gang, will catch the bad guys

223
00:10:37,940 --> 00:10:39,940
even if it costs me my apprentice.

224
00:10:43,940 --> 00:10:45,940
It's my bad luck to be caught by you,

225
00:10:45,940 --> 00:10:47,940
but I was just following orders.

226
00:10:47,940 --> 00:10:49,940
He sold me out after getting what he wanted.

227
00:10:49,940 --> 00:10:51,940
This whole mastermind teacher...

228
00:10:54,940 --> 00:10:56,940
Is it the Eye of Light?